    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Behind the tattered prayer flags of a long-dead civilization reveals a series of six-sided symbols carved into the rock of the wall. Some are merely outlines, while others have concentric  shapes inside them.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>This section of wall is covered with symbols from floor to ceiling. Peering upward, you can faintly make out more symbols stretching above you, and sweeping away millennia of dust from the crook of the wall reveals that the etching continues under your feet.

There's something about the placement of the symbols on the wall that hints at a pattern as yet undiscovered.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>The symbols that cover this section of wall are placed in shallow, independent divots, like the weight of their carving has borne them deeper into the rock. The cumulative effect is that of a large, faceted jewel, awaiting only the correct quality of light to shine.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
